g.text: Solution is imagined like multi-cluster cloud solution with frontend application.
Boxes represent domains, but can be viewed as microservices too.
Arrows represent flow of information in most cases.
- Web portal - UI app for customers to manage their accounts and services
- CDN - serves UI app assets from a bucket
- MCI/Load balancer - redirects trafic to corect region, can be used for disaster recovery too
- Gateway - Proxies requests to coresponding services. Has auth built in for early auth validation
- potentinaly one service depending on the use cases
- db might be document db as potentialy there is a high read rate
- Might be integrated with Services Catalogue
- Responsible for sending orders to CCP
- can be made asynchronous with additional syncer job component
- takes care for customer support cases
- can integrate with internal use ticketing system (Jira?)
- Gateway may be implemented as graphql server depending of other factors
- services are not necessarily rest, but based on the need might be grpc
- all services have security built in, no unprotected access
- based on region, service availability and prices may differ
- Db technologies should be chosen after considering more factors (data type, data accessing, availability)
As the idea is to deliver services to the customers in several different regions
of the globe, good way to do it is to go with multi region cloud solution. That
way the customers can benefit the most, from reduced latency, availability to
resilience. In some cases maybe even some regulatory complience.
With that said, I would design this solution as a kubernetes services kluster
fronted with load balancer in front of which will be the CDN with its features
(assets delivery, chaching, Web application firewall, Geo location locking).
As soultion should be easy to scale if needed, and by requirements theres seems to
be some asynchronous work to be done, microservice architecture would be good
choice to go with, as those are one of the problems it solves.
As interaction with CCP is crucial part of the business there should be high
security and data integrity in place.
